# API Specification

## Base URL

All endpoints prefixed with `/api`. Hosted on Cloudflare Workers.

## Authentication

- **POST /api/auth/register** -- Create account `{ email, name, password }`
- **POST /api/auth/login** -- Returns `{ token: string }` (JWT, 24h expiry)
- **POST /api/auth/refresh** -- Refresh JWT token

JWT passed via `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.
CSRF protection via double-submit cookie pattern on state-changing requests.

## Songs

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | /api/songs | List own songs + shared songs for authenticated user |
| POST | /api/songs | Create song `{ title, description? }` |
| GET | /api/songs/:id | Get song by ID (with note count, collaborator count) |
| PUT | /api/songs/:id | Update song `{ title?, description? }` (owner or editor) |
| DELETE | /api/songs/:id | Delete song and cascade notes (owner only) |

Query params for GET /api/songs: `?filter=owned|shared|all` (default: all), `?sort=updated_at|created_at` (default: updated_at DESC).

## Song Collaborators

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | /api/songs/:id/collaborators | List collaborators for a song |
| POST | /api/songs/:id/collaborators | Invite user `{ email, role: 'editor'|'viewer' }` (owner only) |
| PUT | /api/songs/:id/collaborators/:userId | Update role `{ role }` (owner only) |
| DELETE | /api/songs/:id/collaborators/:userId | Remove collaborator (owner only) |

Access rules: owner has full access, `editor` can CRUD notes, `viewer` can only read.

## Notes

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | /api/songs/:id/notes | List all notes for a song |
| POST | /api/songs/:id/notes | Create note `{ title, track, time, color?, description? }` |
| PUT | /api/songs/:id/notes/:noteId | Update note fields |
| DELETE | /api/songs/:id/notes/:noteId | Delete note |

### Note Constraints

- `track`: integer, 1-8
- `time`: float, 0.0-300.0
- `color`: hex string, default `#3B82F6`
- Unique constraint: one note per (song_id, track, time) -- returns 409 on conflict

## Note History (Ledger)

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | /api/songs/:id/history | List note events for a song (event sourcing ledger) |

Every note create/update/delete writes a row to `note_events` with the action and a JSON snapshot.

## WebSocket (Real-time)

- **GET /api/songs/:id/ws** -- Upgrade to WebSocket, proxied to SongRoom Durable Object

### Messages (server -> client)

```json
{ "type": "note:created", "data": { ...note } }
{ "type": "note:updated", "data": { ...note } }
{ "type": "note:deleted", "data": { "id": "..." } }
{ "type": "user:joined", "data": { "userId": "...", "name": "..." } }
{ "type": "user:left", "data": { "userId": "..." } }
```

### Messages (client -> server)

```json
{ "type": "note:create", "data": { "title": "...", "track": 1, "time": 5.0 } }
{ "type": "note:update", "data": { "id": "...", "title": "..." } }
{ "type": "note:delete", "data": { "id": "..." } }
```

## Rate Limiting

- Auth endpoints: 10 requests/minute per IP
- CRUD endpoints: 100 requests/minute per user
- WebSocket: 60 messages/minute per connection

## Error Response Format

All errors return:

```json
{
  "error": "Human-readable message",
  "code": "MACHINE_READABLE_CODE"
}
```

Common codes: `UNAUTHORIZED`, `FORBIDDEN`, `NOT_FOUND`, `CONFLICT`, `VALIDATION_ERROR`, `RATE_LIMITED`, `INTERNAL_ERROR`.
